data.description: Your Dream Of Living In A Storybook Victorian Home Can Now Be Your Reality! This Historic Home In The Heart of Geneva Has A Tremendous Amount Of Rich History With Original Charm and Character. This Amazing Property Has Been Completely Restored Back To Life. A Chef's Brand New Dream Kitchen Awaits With Granite Countertops, Custom Cabinetry, Stainless Steel Appliances To Include Jenn Air Six Burner Range With Industrial Hood Vent System.  The Original Clawfoot Tub In The Guest Bath Along With Porcelain Shower Head Remains In Prestige Condition! This Home Offers A Library Containing Floor To Ceiling Solid Oak Bookcases Of Which Contain A Custom Bar Area, Grand Dining Room Perfect For Hosting Gatherings With A Reported 1800's Hubbard Brass Light Fixture With Carved Lead Crystal Type Bowl, Multiple Fireplaces Remain Holding The Rich Character Of This Home, Grand Southern Front Porch To Enjoy For Hours While Talking With Friend & Neighbors, 13 Ft. Roaring Ceilings Containing Shiplap And Original Wood Walls,  Original Hardwood Floors Throughout The Majority Of The Home, Copper Gutters And Trim, New Shop With Concrete Slab In Rear Yard, Original Doors With Original Hardware, and SO Much More!!! If Southern Living In A True Victorian Home Is Your Dream, Look No Further! This Amazing Property Will Take You Back To The Early 1900's With All Of Your Modern Day Conveniences! Make Your Appointment To View Today As This Beautiful Rich Piece Of Alabama History Will Not Last Long!
